description: The Wapekute, Indians belonging to the Dakota group, allocate in Darkwood and begin to make prisoners among white settlers and pioneers. Among those kidnapped, there is the husband of Molly Graw, an indomitable woman, willing to do anything to find the man she loves. On his way, Molly finds all sorts of dangers and opponents, and one ally ... Zagor, the Spirit with the Hatchet!
name: La danza degli spiriti

description: Translates Uncanny X-Men Annual #3, Steve Rogers: Super Soldier Annual and Namor: The First Mutant Annual.

Arnstadt, a quiet German city, where we get to meet two old friends again: professor Hans Milius and his alluring student, Sohpie Mutter. Way up in an attic, a strange doll house is found, and it’s mysteriously connected with the disappearance of a little girl in the early 1900s. One century later, it’s Sophie’s turn to disappear! The only clues available to our Dampyr are some mysterious snatches of music heard in a dream and the strange toy house, whose doll-tenants seem to be animated by a strange silent life.
name: Casa di bambole

description: What a grand country, Ireland… grand and desperate! One might be inclined to say that its most typical color, in addition to the myriad shades of green of its verdant pastures, is the bright red of blood that has been shed because of the bitter warfare, no less absurd than fierce, that pits protestants against catholics. And it in this horror scenario that a cruel “Orangeman” takes up his activity anew- an activity that’s seen him on the battlefields these last four centuries, intent on sabotaging any peace negotiations between opposing factions. now it’s Dampyr and Kurjak who are going to put a stop to his march of death and destruction!
name: L’uomo di Belfast

description: From the darkest depths of Wales, an ancestral horror has emerged forth: the Tylwyth Teg, the Little People, who have broken out from the underground world of Annwn in which they were closed up thousands and thousands of years ago. Now it’s the Tylwyth Teg, together with a terrible creature of the lake, that are tormenting the mining village of Llandegant, in the region of Snowdonia, the very area where Harlan and Tesla arrive in search of the writer Dolly MacLaine who seems to have disappeared into thin air. Battling against monstrous bloodthirsty demons, it’s not long before the dampyr and his alluring travel mate realize that the Little People are far less jolly than the way they’re made out to be in fairy tales. Luckily, the pair have a really special ally fighting alongside with them: Amber Tremayne, the striking Mistress of the Night who, according to the terms of an ancient debt contracted at the time of the Roman presence in Britain, keeps watch over the inhabitants of the village…
name: La leggenda di Amber

description: The tower of Dynas Emrys is all that remains of the ancient castle of King Vortigern. And it’s also the passageway that leads down into the underground world of Annwn - the place those ghoulish members of the “Beautiful Family” have come back from: in other words, it’s the place of origin of the Tylwyth Teg, those demons in the service of Black Annis. What has enabled them to start off on their forays again is archaeologist Matthew Shady’s breaking of the magic seal that had kept them imprisoned. Luckily for the imprudent scholar, the protecting aura of Amber Tremayne casts a defensive net over him, and so does that of a born fighter like Kurjak. The match that’s being played out in the village of Llandegant between Annis the Black’s infernal hordes and the team composed of Harlan, Tesla and Amber reaches its epilogue in none other than the well-shaft that extends deep down below Dynas Emreys. Legend has it that way back in ancient times cruel Vortigern, eager to clinch a pact with the obscure forces, flung a young warrior into this well: no ordinary warrior but the offspring of the union between the Roman-Britannic condottiero Macsen Wledig and a woman of demonic nature. The warrior’s name was Emrys, called Aurelio Ambrosio by the Romans, and he was the half-brother of Artos, who in later years would be known by the name of Arthur…
name: Il sigillo nero

description: Whilst they are on the tracks of the mysterious Master who set up a confrontation with them, at a distance, in Northern Ireland, our heroes muse over fragmentary reminiscences of Harlan’s youth, investigate into the mystery of the Vampire of Highgate, the celebrated London cemetery, make the acquaintance of an odd “decommissioned” vampire hunter, Dean Barrymore, and, through the underground passages of London, eventually get to a sort of make-believe Victorian district where, to their amazement, they find the mansion of Carfax Abbey, as imagined by Bram Stoker for his novel “Dracula”. But does this mean that the mysterious Master of London might be none other than the famed Conte?
name: Il vampiro di Highgate

description: Last issue of Nick Raider. He will finally marry his lover Violet McGraw.
name: Progetto Dakota
Vivere e morire a New York

description:
The only thing worse than getting on the bad side of gangsters is capturing the ghosts of the some of the most historically notorious figures in organized crime. And when you upset the spirits of the mafia, you better be prepared to go to the mattresses. But when the Ghostbusters find themselves in Purgatory they need to find a way out, and fast, before they end up spending an eternity in Hell.

The Trade paperback of the Other Side storyline
name: Vol. 1

description: Dynomite is the hapless hero who finds himself locked in an ongoing struggle against a nasty, one-handed pimp named Kane who has kidnapped his girl, gotten him locked up, and has a real flair for the dramatic. Will Dynomite ever rescue his lady, or at least get some much-needed sexual healing? Find out in this collection presented by IDW Publishing and 5-D Comics including bonus materials straight from the Wayans Bros.!

THE AWARD-WINNING, BESTSELLING, POWERHOUSE CREATIVE TEAM BEHIND DAREDEVIL, HALO AND THE AVENGERS UNLEASHES ITS BOLDEST PROJECT YET! SCARLET! This is the comic experience of the year! The first creator-owned series by one of the most successful teams in all of modern comics, SCARLET is the story of a woman pushed to the edge by all that's wrong with the world. A woman who decides to stand up and fight back. A woman who will not back down. A woman who discovers within herself the power to start a modern American revolution! In the vein of ALIAS, POWERS and JINX, SCARLET debuts a fascinating new comics character who, with every issue, reveals new things about herself against a completely original backdrop of intrigue and drama. This Premiere collection of the first creator-owned series by Bendis since POWERS - and the first-ever creator-owned series by Maleev - includes tons of extras, a look at the first-issue script by Bendis with new illustrations by Maleev, an all-star cover gallery and more!
name: Book One
